About IPV4:
IPV4 is an unreliable datagram protocol."Best effort to delivery"
No flow control or error control. 
It consists of two parts 
1.)Header 
2.)Data

Header contains different fields: 
        Version- which version it is, either ipv4 or ipv6.
        header length-length of the header field in 4 byte words. 4<=HLEN<=15
        Total length
        Time to live 
        Protocol -(ICMP, IGMP, TCP, UDP)
        Header checksum 
        source ip address
        destination ip address
        identification 
        flag 
OSI Model of layers:
         Application layer
         Transport layer 
         Network layer
         Data link layer
